<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561402>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3. Manota corniculata sp. n. (A, B, D holotype, C paratype). A. Hypopygium, dorsal view. B. Hypopygium, ventral view. C. Gonostylus, dorsal view. D. Hypoproct and aedeagus, ventral view. Scale 0.1 mm. aed = apex of aedeagus, aeda = aedeagal apodeme, ce = cercus, dm = dorsal medial margin of gonocoxa, fll = finger-like lobe, gs = gonostylus, gx = gonocoxa, gxa = gonocoxal apodeme, hpr = hypoproct, jxd = the more dorsal juxtagonostylar megaseta, jxv = the more ventral juxtagonostylar megaseta, plg = posterolateral lobe of gonocoxa, pll = plate-like lobe, psl = setae of parastylar lobe, st9 = sternite 9, tg9 = posterior margin of tergite 9, vm = ventral medial margin of gonocoxa." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4561402/files/figure.png" .
